## Rules

1. **Take a `playwright-cli` snapshot before writing any locator.** Navigate to each page in the running app and capture the live ARIA tree. Derive every locator from what the snapshot actually shows — not from file names, source code inference, or naming conventions.
2. **Source code answers navigation questions only — never locator questions.** Use source code to find: the correct URL to navigate to, which HTTP routes exist, Angular state names, Rails model attribute names. Do NOT read source code to find element IDs or CSS classes and then assume they match the live DOM — they may differ at runtime. If you need an element's ID, find it via `playwright-cli eval "document.querySelector('.visible-class').id"` on the live page.
3. All page objects extend `BasePage<T>` with own type as generic parameter
4. All components extend `BaseComponent<T>`, scoped to `rootComponent` locator
5. Assertions belong in tests only — page objects NEVER import `expect`
6. Locators are `private readonly`, exposed via getter methods
7. When source code provides an element ID, prefer `locator('#id')` over `getByRole()` to avoid strict-mode ambiguity. Use `getByRole()` when IDs are not available.
8. Navigation methods return the destination page object (fluent pattern)
9. Every page/component implements `waitForLoad()` returning `this as T`
10. All locators use `.describe()` for trace clarity
11. All async functions must use `await`

